AlternateCase Scenario

The alternative release scenario at the facility involves the release of 54000 pounds of anhydrous ammonia, under a release rate of 1320 lbs/min. over a 40 minute period, due to a fracture in a =" liquid bypass line.  Under alternative release weather conditions, wind speed 6.7 MPH, stability class D, resulting ammonia could travel 0.5 miles before dispersing enough to no longer pose a hazard to the public. (Toxic endpoint @ 0.14 mg/l :basis ERPG-2)

-The Alternative release scenario is unlikely for the following reasons:
    -Industry standards were followed for the manufacture and quality control of the lines 
      and IIAR guidelines followed for installation;
    -Ammonia is not corrosive in this service and the vessels are relatively new;
